1: -module(vehicle_SUITE).
    2: -include("public_transport.hrl").
    3: -include("time.hrl").
    4: -include_lib("common_test/include/ct.hrl").
    5: -include_lib("eunit/include/eunit.hrl"). %% For assertion macros
    6: 
    7: -export([ checkin_ok_case/1
    8:         , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case/1
    9:         , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case/1
   10:         , next_stop_reached_case/1
   11:         , next_stop_not_reached_case/1
   12:         , target_stop_reached_case/1
   13:         , increment_boarding_passenger_case/1
   14:         , new_time_not_driving_case/1]).
   15: 
   16: -export([ all/0
   17:         , init_per_testcase/2
   18:         , end_per_testcase/2]).
   19: 
   20: all() ->
   21:   [ checkin_ok_case
   22:   , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case
   23:   , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case
   24:   , next_stop_reached_case
   25:   , next_stop_not_reached_case
   26:   , target_stop_reached_case
   27:   , increment_boarding_passenger_case
   28:   , new_time_not_driving_case
   29:   ].
   30: 
   31: init_per_testcase(Config) ->
   32:   put(id, ?MODULE),
   33:   put(module, ?MODULE_STRING),
   34:   logger:start_link("log"),
   35:   vehicle_supervisor:start_link(),
   36:   StartStop = gen_server_mock:start(stop, startstop, strict),
   37:   TargetStop = gen_server_mock:start(stop, targetstop, strict),
   38:   Time = gen_server_mock:start_global(time, time, strict),
   39:   L1 = gen_server_mock:start(line, l1, strict),
   40:   S1 = gen_server_mock:start(stop, s1, strict),
   41:   P1 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p1, strict),
   42:   P2 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p2, strict),
   43:   P3 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p3, strict),
   44:   P4 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p4, strict),
   45: 
   46:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, ?GET_NUMBER, 1),
   47:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_OTHER_END, TargetStop}, StartStop),
   48: 
   49:   Config ++ [ {startstop, StartStop}
   50:             , {targetstop, TargetStop}
   51:             , {time, Time}
   52:             , {l1, L1}
   53:             , {s1, S1}
   54:             , {p1, P1}
   55:             , {p2, P2}
   56:             , {p3, P3}
   57:             , {p4, P4}
   58:             ].
   59: 
   60: init_per_testcase(TestCase, Config) ->
   61:   UpdatedConfig = init_per_testcase(Config),
   62:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, UpdatedConfig),
   63:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, UpdatedConfig),
   64:   Time = ?config(time, UpdatedConfig),
   65:   L1 = ?config(l1, UpdatedConfig),
   66:   HasThreeCapacity = lists:member(TestCase, [ checkin_ok_case
   67:                                             , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case
   68:                                             , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case
   69:                                             , new_time_not_driving_case
   70:                                             ]),
   71:   HasFourCapacity = lists:member(TestCase, [ next_stop_reached_case
   72:                                            , next_stop_not_reached_case
   73:                                            , target_stop_reached_case
   74:                                            , increment_boarding_passenger_case
   75:                                            ]),
   76:   Vehicle = vehicle_supervisor:start_vehicle(if
   77:                                                HasThreeCapacity -> 3;
   78:                                                HasFourCapacity -> 4
   79:                                              end, L1, TargetStop, bus),
   80:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(Time, {?SUBSCRIBE, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
   81:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_IN, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
   82: 
   83:   [{vehicle, Vehicle}|UpdatedConfig].
   84: 
   85: 
   86: 
   87: end_per_testcase(_TestCase, Config) ->
   88:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
   89:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
   90:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
   91:   L1 = ?config(l1, Config),
   92:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
   93:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
   94:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
   95:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
   96:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
   97:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
   98:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(StartStop)),
   99:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(TargetStop)),
  100:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(Time)),
  101:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(L1)),
  102:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(S1)),
  103:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P1)),
  104:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P2)),
  105:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P3)),
  106:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P4)),
  107:   gen_server_mock:stop(StartStop),
  108:   gen_server_mock:stop(TargetStop),
  109:   gen_server_mock:stop(Time),
  110:   gen_server_mock:stop(L1),
  111:   gen_server_mock:stop(S1),
  112:   gen_server_mock:stop(P1),
  113:   gen_server_mock:stop(P2),
  114:   gen_server_mock:stop(P3),
  115:   gen_server_mock:stop(P4),
  116:   vehicle_supervisor:stop_vehicle(Vehicle),
  117:   logger:stop(),
  118:   Config.
  119: 
  120: 
  121: checkin_ok_case(Config) ->
  122:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  123:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  124:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  125:   L1 = ?config(l1, Config),
  126:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  127:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  128:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  129:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  130:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  131:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  132: 
  133:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_NEXT_STOP, TargetStop, StartStop}, {S1, 5}),
  134:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(Time, ?GET_CURRENT_TIME, 1234),
  135:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  136:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 0, true).
  137: 
  138: boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case(Config) ->
  139:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  140:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  141:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  142:   L1 = ?config(l1, Config),
  143:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  144:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  145:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  146:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  147:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  148:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  149: 
  150:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 4, true),
  151:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  152:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  153: 
  154:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_NEXT_STOP, TargetStop, StartStop}, {S1, 5}),
  155:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(Time, ?GET_CURRENT_TIME, 1234),
  156:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  157:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok),
  158:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P4), nok).
  159: 
  160: boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case(Config) ->
  161:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  162:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  163:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  164:   L1 = ?config(l1, Config),
  165:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  166:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  167:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  168:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  169:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  170:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  171: 
  172:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 3, true),
  173:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  174:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  175: 
  176:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_NEXT_STOP, TargetStop, StartStop}, {S1, 5}),
  177:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(Time, ?GET_CURRENT_TIME, 1234),
  178:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  179:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok).
  180: 
  181: next_stop_reached_case(Config) ->
  182:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  183:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  184:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  185:   L1 = ?config(l1, Config),
  186:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  187:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  188:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  189:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  190:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  191:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  192: 
  193:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 3, true),
  194:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  195:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  196: 
  197:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_NEXT_STOP, TargetStop, StartStop}, {S1, 5}),
  198:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(Time, ?GET_CURRENT_TIME, 1234),
  199:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  200:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok),
  201: 
  202:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P1, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, leave),
  203:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P2, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, stay),
  204:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P3, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, stay),
  205:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(S1, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_IN, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  206:   vehicle:?NEW_TIME(Vehicle, 1234+5, true).
  207:

  269:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),

  297: 
  298:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(L1, {?GET_NEXT_STOP, TargetStop, StartStop}, {S1, 5}),
  299:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(Time, ?GET_CURRENT_TIME, 1234),
  300:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
